urlLink Changing Organizational Partnerships to Build an Information Literacy Program in the Extended Campus Environment   This was presented by Leslie Wykoff, Director of Vancouver Information Systems, Washington State University Vancouver; and Karen Diller, Assistant Campus Librarian, Washington State University Vancouver at In Living the Future 11: Tucson: University of Arozona, 1998  From the site:  At WSU Vancouver, the Library, Computing and Educational Television Departments merged into the cohesive service organization called Vancouver Information Services (VIS), enabling the campus to develop and integrate program in information literacy. This paper will review the trials and triumphs of merging information technology departments and show how VIS is integral to the campus information literacy goals.